.TH "UNLZX" "1" "2026" "unlzx 2.0" "General Commands Manual"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
unlzx - extract or list files from Amiga LZX archives
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]unlzx\f[R] [\f[B]-v\f[R]|\f[B]-x\f[R]] [\f[B]-c\f[R]]
[\f[I]archive\f[R] \&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]unlzx\f[R] extracts or lists the contents of LZX archives.
.PP
LZX is a lossless data compression format based on the LZ77 algorithm,
originally developed for the Amiga computer platform.
It uses Huffman coding with two compression modes: stored (uncompressed)
and packed (compressed).
Merged blocks spanning multiple files within a single compressed stream
are also supported.
.PP
Each extracted file is verified against a CRC-32 checksum stored in the
archive header.
A mismatch is reported but does not abort further processing.
.PP
Without any option, \f[B]unlzx\f[R] defaults to extraction mode
(\f[B]-x\f[R]).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-c\f[R]
Read the archive from standard input instead of a named file.
.TP
\f[B]-v\f[R]
List the contents of the archive: file sizes, timestamps, protection
attributes, and filenames.
Does not extract any file.
.TP
\f[B]-x\f[R]
Extract files from the archive into the current directory, recreating
sub-directory trees as needed.
This is the default mode.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
All archives processed successfully.
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
An error occurred during extraction or listing (corrupt data, I/O error,
invalid archive).
.TP
\f[B]2\f[R]
Invalid usage (unknown option or missing file arguments).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
List the contents of an archive:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
unlzx -v game.lzx
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Extract all files from an archive:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
unlzx game.lzx
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Extract from standard input:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
cat game.lzx | unlzx -c
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]lha\f[R](1), \f[B]unar\f[R](1)
